@startuml
!include ../includes/appsec-style.puml
title AppSec Process 02: Homegrown CI Security Gates (Shift Left)

' Purpose: Prevent new critical/high risk findings from merging while keeping developer flow.
'          AppCode is used to correlate results across tools and route ownership.

start

partition "Pull Request" {
  :Create PR;
  :Attach AppCode metadata (repo tags, build vars, artifact labels);
  :Build + unit tests;
}

partition "Build & Quality Gates" {
  :Static analysis (SonarQube)<<gate>>;
  :80% coverage threshold<<gate>>;
}

partition "Security Gates (CI)" {
  :GHAS SAST (CodeQL);
  :GHAS secrets;
  :GHAS dependency review / SCA;
  :Trivy IaC/config scan;
  :Trivy image scan (if container);
  :Optional Coverity (language gap SAST);
}

partition "Triage" {
  :Normalize + dedupe findings (key = AppCode);
  if (New critical/high?) then (Yes)
    :Assign owner (AppCode -> team);
    :Fix or mitigate;
  else (No)
    :Proceed;
  endif
}

partition "Gate" {
  :Merge decision<<gate>>;
}

partition "After Merge" {
  :Main branch scans (GHAS/SonarQube/Trivy);
  :Publish SBOM (Trivy) + link to AppCode;
  :CD deploy;
  :DAST schedule (InsightAppSec);
  :IAST in QA (Seeker);
}

note right
Key message: **"No new critical/high" merge gate**.
AppCode ties every finding to an owner and an SLA.
end note

stop
@enduml
